MARKET_DYNAMICS:
* Supply/demand: Prices adjust based on local availability
* Regional variations: Different sectors value resources differently
* Distance premium: Farther transport typically = higher prices
* Player impact: High trading volume temporarily affects sector values
* Faction modifiers: Reputation affects pricing at faction-controlled ports

ACQUISITION_METHODS:
Trading:
  method: Buy low at production sectors, sell high at shortage sectors
  strategy: Efficient routes between complementary ports
  optimization: Maximize cargo capacity, optimize travel paths

Production:
  method: Establish colonies to generate specific resources
  investment: Infrastructure for improved efficiency
  automation: Automated generation over time
  specialization: Focus planets on optimal commodity output

Combat:
  method: Attack traders/pirates to seize cargo
  risk: Combat costs turns, potential ship loss
  salvage: Abandoned ships/stations may contain resources

Exploration:
  method: Discover uncharted sectors with valuable deposits
  rare_materials: Locate quantum shards in dangerous regions
  route_mapping: Find efficient trade routes between distant markets

CONSTRAINTS:
* Population only from Sector 1 population hub of each region
* Quantum Crystals require 5 Quantum Shards
* Port classes strictly determine buy/sell inventory
* Cargo lost on ship destruction
* Credits never lost (virtual storage)
* Team treasury limited to 13 resource types
* Rare materials require specific location types (asteroids, nebulae)

